notesStmt.note: Title supplied by cataloger; author from title page for first section (f. 1r).
Other title, Imperialium institutionum libri IV, is from Zacour-Hirsch.
Incipit: Proemium. Legibus &c. tum pacis tum belli tempore respublica regi debet; quare Justinianus veraqure precise necessaria comperiens ... (p. i).
Explicit: ... ubi Deo propitio plenius saturentur ut monemur in ss. ult. h[oc] t[itulum] (p. 386).

msContents.summary: Four books of commentary on Justinian's Institutiones, one of the major Roman law texts, with an index.

supportDesc.extent: 222 leaves : 198 x 140 (141 x 95) mm. bound to 204 x 144 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, 222; [i], 1-88, [i], 89-182, [i], 183-201, [ii], 202-289, [i]. 290-386, [lii]; contemporary pagination in ink, upper outer corners.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a cursive script by a single hand.

decoDesc.decoNote: Title borders, vignettes, and tailpieces in pen and black ink on title page, opposite p. 89 and 182, p. 289, opposite p. 289, p. 386, [389], [393], [436]. Fold-out diagram of kinship relationships, "Haec est Arbor Civilis," decorated with red (between p. 201 and 202).

history.provenance: "Ex libris M. von Wilmersdoerffer, 1897," printed color bookplate inside upper cover.
